ources/tools/index.php"><span class="leftnav">Tools</span></a></li><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/sdks.php"><span class="leftnav">SDKs</span></a></li><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/sample-code/index.php"><span class="leftnav">Sample Code</span></a></li><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/development-boards/index.php"><span class="leftnav">Development Boards</span></a></li><li class="active expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/index.php"><span class="leftnav">Drivers</span></a><ul class="leftnavsub"><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/open-source-mali-gpus-linux-kernel-device-drivers.php"><span class="leftnav">Open Source Mali GPUs Linux Kernel Device Drivers</span></a></li><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/open-source-mali-gpu-android-kernel-device-drivers.php"><span class="leftnav">Open Source Mali GPU Android Kernel Device Drivers</span></a></li><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/open-source-mali-gpus-linux-exadri2-and-x11-display-drivers.php"><span class="leftnav">Open Source Mali GPUs Linux EXA/DRI2 and X11 Display Drivers</span></a></li><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/open-source-mali-gpus-android-gralloc-module.php"><span class="leftnav">Open Source Mali GPUs Android Gralloc Module</span></a></li><li class="navarrow"><div class="navarrowimage"></div></li><li class="active expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/open-source-mali-gpus-ump-user-space-drivers-source-code.php"><span class="leftnav">Open Source Mali GPUs UMP User Space Drivers Source Code</span></a><ul class="leftnavsub"></ul></li><li class="expanded thirdbottom"></li></ul></li><li class="expanded"><a href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/documentation/index.php"><span class="leftnav">Documentation</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="bodyarea"><div class="centersection"><div class="centerwrapper"><div class="centercontent"><div class="centercontent_text"><h1>Open Source Mali GPUs UMP User Space Drivers Source Code</h1><h2>UMP User Space Source Code under Apache License</h2>This
 package contains the source code which defines the UMP (Unified Memory 
Provider) user space API Source Code For Mali GPUs Linux UMP Library 
Under Apache License.<br>&nbsp;<br>This is the UMP (Unified Memory 
Provider) user space library that can be used together with the UMP 
kernel device driver. It implements the UMP user space API, which offers
 an easy to use access to shareable memory for user space application.<p>This package is required by the Android Gralloc module and X11 EXA/DRI2 module.</p></div><div id="processortabs" class="modernbricksmenu2"><script type="text/javascript" language="javascript">var selectedtab=0;</script><ul><li><a class="selected" href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/open-source-mali-gpus-ump-user-space-drivers-source-code.php?tab=FEATURES%20&amp;%20BENEFITS" rel="tcontent13465"><span class="tabbefore"></span><span class="tabcenter"><span class="tabspan">FEATURES &amp; BENEFITS</span></span><span class="tabafter"></span></a></li></ul><ul><li><a class="" href="http://www.malideveloper.com/developer-resources/drivers/open-source-mali-gpus-ump-user-space-drivers-source-code.php?tab=LATEST%20RELEASES" rel="tcontent13464"><span class="tabbefore"></span><span class="tabcenter"><span class="tabspan">LATEST RELEASES</span></span><span class="tabafter"></span></a></li></ul></div><div style="display: block;" class="tabcontent" id="tcontent13465"><br><div class="mainbodycontent"><p style="margin:0cm 0cm 0pt">The UMP module handles:</p><ul><li><div style="margin:0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;Access
 to allocated UMP memory through a secure ID. This enables memory to be 
shared across different applications, drivers and hardware components to
 facilitate zero-copy operations</div></li><li><div style="margin:0cm 0cm 0pt">The physical address information required to set up an MMU or MPU table</div></li><li><div style="margin:0cm 0cm 0pt">A method to map UMP memory into CPU address space, to enable reading and writing</div></li></ul><div class="clear"></div></div></div><div style="display: none;" class="tabcontent" id="tcontent13464"><br><div class="mainbodycontent"><h2></h2><h1>Mali GPUs UMP User Space Drivers Source Code</h1><div style="border-bottom:#d2d2d2 1px solid;border-left:#d2d2d2 1px solid;width:500px;height:160px;overflow:auto;border-top:#d2d2d2 1px solid;border-right:#d2d2d2 1px solid"><table style="width: 450px;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td><h1>THE APACHE LICENSE FOR MALI GPUS UMP USER SPACE DRIVERS SOURCE CODE</h1><p>The
